    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown\u00a0onion[s]</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>\u00a0in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-lemon-risotto-with-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large drizzle of\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>\u00a0with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-6 min or until softened but not browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-lemon-risotto-with-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, stir your <strong>arborio rice</strong>\u00a0into the pan, making sure the grains of rice are coated in oil</p><p>Add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for a further 30 secs or until it has evaporated</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-low</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-lemon-risotto-with-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 1/3 of the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and stir continuously with a wooden spoon until it has absorbed into the rice</p><p>Continue to add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong>, a ladle at a time, stirring more or less continuously for 25-30 min, until all the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your\u00a0<strong>risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-lemon-risotto-with-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the risotto is cooking, cut the <strong>lemon[s] </strong>in half</p><p>Peel the skin off your<strong> smoked\u00a0mackerel fillet[s]</strong> and discard</p><p>Tear the <strong>smoked mackerel</strong> into small, rough pieces (watch out for small bones!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-lemon-risotto-with-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once all the stock has been absorbed, add the<strong> smoked mackerel pieces</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>to the pan</p><p>Continue to cook until all of the butter is melted and the risotto is creamy</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-lemon-risotto-with-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the pan from the heat and stir in your<strong>\u00a0soft cheese </strong>and<strong> </strong>the juice\u00a0of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong>\u00a0into the risotto</p><p>Season very generously with <strong>pepper</strong> (use much more than you normally would!) \u2013 this is your <strong>smoked mackerel\u00a0& lemon risotto</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then gently pat dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-and-lemon-risotto-with-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoked mackerel & lemon\u00a0risotto</strong> in a bowl topped with a handful of <strong>salad </strong>and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Drizzle the salad<strong> </strong>with<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
